- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a new regression model that enforces sparsity and low-rankness of the tensor coefficient, and evaluates it on simulated datasets and fMRI data. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed model can be applied to image data represented as tensors. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed model can be used for prediction tasks in various scientific fields. 
- cs.ST (Statistics): The paper discusses the optimization method used to solve the proposed model and proves a tighter convergence rate over three-order tensor data. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the optimization method used to solve the proposed model and evaluates its efficiency on simulated datasets and fMRI data.
